    {
        "content": "<p>Cyclicity is done in <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/22885\">#22885</a> with the statement</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">instance</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">K</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">L</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Finite</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">K</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Finite</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">L</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Field</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">K</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Field</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">L</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Algebra</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">K</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">L</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IsCyclic</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">L</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≃ₐ</span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">K</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">L</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>(cc <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"630477\">@Scott Carnahan</span>)<br>\nSome students at the PKU/BICMR workshop Feb 12-16 also attempted to work on this (that's why I didn't resume working on this until now), and I hope they see this ...</p>",
